[SN]TITLE[SN]
Kent Police issue warning over missing hospital patient

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Police are hunting for a man who has gone missing from hospital and have warned the public not to approach him.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Glenn Picot, 34, was last seen at Maidstone Hospital at 13:10 BST on Friday.
Kent Police have described Mr Picot as "vulnerable", saying he is "not getting the care he needs" while away from hospital.
They said it is possible he is travelling to Jersey where it is believed he has relatives.
He is described as 5ft 9in tall and of slim build. He is white, with brown eyes, has cropped brown hair and a long beard.
He also has tattoos on his back, scars on both arms, on his head and above his left eyebrow and also two piercings in his left ear.
Insp Jody Gagen-Cook said: "Mr Picot is vulnerable, if you see him do not approach him and call the police."
